:'''Gao Tang:''' Oh, ask away. I have much to share, as long as it's about food.
:<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502010702_140-->
:<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502010702_140-->
:{{DIcon|Talk}} Is it true? That there's no good food in the Starskiff Haven?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502107103-->
::'''Gao Tang:''' Strictly speaking, Starskiff Haven's food is enough to sate your hunger. Whether it tastes good is another matter.
::'''Gao Tang:''' Without stringent selection nor prudent handling of ingredients, I refuse to accept food that has been made haphazardly.
::'''Gao Tang:''' But don't worry. Starskiff Haven's food does not represent Xianzhou's culinary landscape. You can still find restaurants dedicated to the craft here.
::'''Gao Tang:''' If nothing else, once you've tried the dishes at the Garden of Gourmet, I'm sure you will lose interest in this subpar fare.
:;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:{{DIcon|Talk}} What kind of food does the Garden of Gourmet serve?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502107108-->
::'''Gao Tang:''' The restaurant's been making sturgeons recently. This type of fish returns once every fifty years, and is a key ingredient in "Five Lords of Anhe River."
::'''Gao Tang:''' In the Garden of Gourmet, we extract the three crunchiest bones from the tail, boil them in a broth of myriad herbs, then grill them using fresh goat's fat paste. At the final stage, we slow fry them till the meaty bones are caramelized and crisp.
::'''Gao Tang:''' Any step that's not up to snuff in this process, and I'll dump the dish entirely. This is also why the Garden of Gourmet has no menu &mdash; we only serve one table a day.
::'''Gao Tang:''' No such thing as food too fine, or meat too minced. Those of Xianzhou have lived for a thousand years, we must be meticulous with what goes in our mouths.
:;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:{{DIcon|Talk}} You speak with such passion when discussing cuisine.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502107113-->
::'''Gao Tang:''' We are all, in some way, shaped by our food. You wouldn't want to be made shoddily, would you?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I wouldn't.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502107115-->
:::'''Gao Tang:''' I thought so.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502107120-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502107120-->
:::'''Gao Tang:''' I notice you are an Outworlder. Your food tapestry must be limited, so you must make wiser choices.
:::'''Gao Tang:''' To be strict with what you eat is to be strict with the "reason why we are people."
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I'm fine either way.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502107117-->
